Hi @yustoris,
Thank you for providing the details. I can repro this issue. I might know what happened -- While running `python detect.py --source (any image file) --weights yolov5s.onnx`, did you see it complains that onnxruntime is not installed and then it installs onnxruntime directly although you have onnxruntime-gpu already?

If so, I think running detect.py will always be CPU-only ONNXRuntime anyway. Could you please try to comment this line: https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/blob/070af88108e5675358fd783aae9d91e927717322/detect.py#L89, `pip uninstall -y onnxruntime && pip uninstall -y onnxruntime-gpu && pip install onnxruntime-gpu` again, run `python detect.py --weights yolov5s.onnx --device 0` and see whether it can use CUDA normally? At least it works for me. (I am using CUDA 11.4 as well)

However, the CUDA performance looks worse from my end.

@jcwchen 
Thank you for your investigation.

Sorry not to report that I already commented out that line on `detect.py`.
Then, I tried out `pip uninstall -y onnxruntime && pip uninstall -y onnxruntime-gpu && pip install onnxruntime-gpu` and `python detect.py --weights yolov5s.onnx --device 0` again, but the result is the same.

What is wrong with my side?
Hey no worries -- glad we have the same thought. Could you please share your output of `nvcc --version` and `nvidia-smi`. Also which cudnn version do you use? Thank you
Thanks for the advanced help. I noticed the `nvcc` command is not available in my environment, so it seems that the installation of cudnn has been failed. So, I'll try to re-installation of cudnn.

After re-install cudnn 8, I was able to run the model on CUDAExecutorProvider, i.e., GPU (Unfortunately, the performance degraded as you said).
Then, we can close this ticket. Thank you all anyway.

> 
> 
> After re-install cudnn 8, I was able to run the model on CUDAExecutorProvider, i.e., GPU (Unfortunately, the performance degraded as you said). Then, we can close this ticket. Thank you all anyway.

This might be because cuda 11.2 is usually slower than Cuda 10.2. Is this 10-20 percent slower?

The solution would be to install older version of onxxruntimes and cuda 10.2 and cudnn 7 i think.
Ok, let us know. 60X slower is even slower than on CPU.
